CSS
1.Example
 body {
  background-color: lightblue;
}

h1 {
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  text-align: block;
}

p {
  font-family: verdana;
  font-size: 20px;
}
2. CSS- Background 
div {
  background-color: green;
  opacity: 0.3;
}
3.Background Image 
body {
  background-image: url("bgdesert.jpg");
}
4. Repeating 
 background-repeat: repeat-x;
- Position of the background image
 background-position: right top;
-Specify that the background image should scroll with the rest of the page:
background-attachment: scroll;

5. CSS Margins 
margin-top
margin-right
margin-bottom
margin-left

6. margin: 25px 50px 75px;
top margin is 25px
right and left margins are 50px
bottom margin is 75px

7. p.italic {
  font-style: italic;
}

8.position
div.relative {
  position: relative;
  left: 30px;
  border: 3px solid #73AD21;
}
9. Also, with display: inline-block, the top and bottom margins/paddings are respected, but with display: inline they are not.

Compared to display: block, the major difference is that display: inline-block does not add a line-break after the element, so the element can sit next to other elements.

10. Alignment 
.center {
  margin: auto;
  width: 50%;
  border: 3px solid green;
  padding: 10px;
}

11.color-keyword
body {
  background-image: url("paper.gif");
}

div {
  background-color: transparent;
}

12. CSS Shadow Effects
h1 {
  text-shadow: 2px 2px;
}
h1 {
  text-shadow: 2px 2px red;
}
h1 {
  color: white;
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #000000;
}

13. CSS Object-Position
img {
  width: 200px;
  height: 300px;
  object-fit: cover;
}

14. Button 
.button {
  background-color: #4CAF50; /* Green */
  border: none;
  color: white;
  padding: 15px 32px;
  text-align: center;
  text-decoration: none;
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: 16px;
}
15. CSS Multi-column Properties
div {
  column-count: 3;
  column-gap: 40px;
  column-rule-style: solid;
  column-rule-width: 1px;
  column-rule-color: lightblue;
  column-rule: 1px solid lightblue;

}
16. CSS image-object fit 
img {
  width: 200px;
  height: 300px;
  object-fit: cover;
}
